data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** because a new non-expression overload is preferred. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & full-path nested

**Two related changes:**

- **Sibling complex types**: `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column silently. EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`), which **will break existing schemas/migrations**.
- **Nested complex types**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** ŌĆö pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
// Sibling complex types
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// Nested complex types ŌĆö preserve old column name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
